- `@left` and `@right` are pointers to the two elements that are being sorted. `@left` points to the element that is to the left of `@left`, and `@right` points to the element that is to the right of `@right`.
- `@size -= 1` is a conditional that decrements the size by one, so that we can keep track of how many elements are in the array.
- `@left, @right` are the two elements that are being sorted using TimSort. `@left` is smaller than `@right`, so they are swapped using a binary operation.

